intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of this course students will be able to:
Design, employ and evaluate programs to access big data repositories in a massively parallel manner;
Describe and contrast the internals of the design and implementation of current cloud data storage and processing systems; 
Identify and discuss issues related to the scalability and efficiency challenges when processing complex queries/algorithms against big data systems, and propose ways of addressing said challenges;
Demonstrate that they have mastered the required background knowledge to pursue graduate studies in the fields of cloud systems and big data.
